SIMPLE: none
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: None
<hw>None</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a. & pron.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>none</ets>, <ets>non</ets>, <ets>nan</ets>, <ets>no</ets>,
<ets>na</ets>, AS. <ets>n⟦amac⟧n</ets>, fr. <ets>ne</ets> not +
<ets>⟦amac⟧n</ets> one. ⟦root⟧193. See <er>No</er>, <pos>a.</pos> &
<pos>adv.</pos>, <er>One</er>, and cf. <er>Non-</er>, <er>Null</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>No one; not one; not anything; -- frequently used
also partitively, or as a plural, not any.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is <qex>none</qex> that doeth good; no, not one.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xiv. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Six days ye shall gather it, but on the seventh day, which is the
Sabbath, in it there shall be <qex>none</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xvi.
26.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Terms of peace yet <qex>none</qex>⟦br⟧
Vouchsafed or sought.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>None</qex> of their productions are extant.</q>
<rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>No; not any; -- used adjectively before a vowel, in
old style; <as>as, thou shalt have <ex>none</ex> assurance of thy
life</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>None of</b></col>, <cd>not at all; not; nothing of; --
used emphatically.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧They knew that I was <xex>none of</xex>
the register that entered their admissions in the universities.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Fuller.</au> -- <col><b>None-so-pretty</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>,
<cd>the <spn>Saxifraga umbrosa</spn>. See <cref>London pride</cref>
<sd>(a)</sd>, under <er>London</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>None</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: None
<hw>None</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>Same as
<er>Nones</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noneffective</ent>⟦br⟧
